# Route Conflict — Fix app.js Before Testing

Your current app.js has a conflict:

```
app.use('/api/v1/admin/businesses', adminBusinessRouter);  ← OLD (line 101)
app.use('/api/v1/admin', adminRouter);                    ← NEW (line 102)
```

The old `adminBusinessRouter` from `business.routes.js` is still mounted. Express will hit it FIRST for `/api/v1/admin/businesses`, shadowing the new admin routes.

## Fix — 2 steps:

**Step 1:** In `app.js`, remove line 101:
```js
// DELETE this line:
app.use('/api/v1/admin/businesses', adminBusinessRouter);

// DELETE the import too (lines 7-9):
import businessRouter, {
  adminBusinessRouter,          // ← remove this
} from './src/routes/api/v1/business.routes.js';
```

**Step 2:** In `business.routes.js`, delete the block at the bottom (lines 81-94):
```js
// DELETE everything below:
export const adminBusinessRouter = Router();
adminBusinessRouter.use(verifyToken, requireAdmin);
adminBusinessRouter.get('/', ...);
adminBusinessRouter.post('/upgrade-plan', ...);
```

After this fix, all admin business routes are handled exclusively by `admin.routes.js`. Restart the server, then run the tests below.
